ed later in the week.  \r\n\r\nWe look forward to seeing you next Friday! \r\n','','10:15 am',1106677007,4,1,1,0,1,1),(143,'Please see below','Other','0','','0','',45,'','Calm','Overcast with slight drizzle',24,35,'Temporarily closed','Mt. Baker is temporarily closed this Monday through Thursday and we plan to REOPEN FRIDAY JANUARY 28TH at 9:00am.  We need about 6 inches of new snow in order to reopen.  Mountain forecasts were initially calling for snow Wed-Sun this week, but it has remained warm so far. . . . we are looking for that freezing level  to D-R-O-P.  More specific info for Friday will be available by mid-day Thursday after we take another look at the snow conditions and see what kind of weather moves in tonight.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll keep you posted here as we know more.\r\n','','3:06 pm',1106780986,4,1,0,0,1,0),(144,'Please see below','Other','trace','','trace','with 2 inches new on Pan Dome',32,'','Calm','Snowing Lightly',20,30,'Temporarily closed - see below for details','Mt. Baker remains temporarily closed today as the season has stalled while we are waiting on a bit more snow.  On the good side, it is currently  snowing lightly up on the mountain, and we have received some new snow.  We are still looking for about 10-12 inches of additional snow before we can resume operations.  \r\n\r\nLooking at our best mountain forecasts, it realistically looks like it will be about another 5 to 7 days before the currently forecasted weather brings us enough snow to start up the lifts again.  We will be updating this site and our snow phones at 360-671-0211 daily weather information by 9:00am each day.\r\n\r\nLooking back at our weather records from 1976 which was a similar type of winter, it snowed 7 feet in mid February and we had a huge amount of snow in March.  We are anticipating . . and of course hoping for . . .a similar weather change soon and will keep you posted.\r\n','','10:36 am',1106851134,4,1,1,0,1,1),(145,'Please see below','Other','trace','','trace','',35,'','Calm','Overcast',20,30,'see below\r\n','Mt. Baker remains closed while we wait on a little more snow, However, we did received a trace of new snow both Thursday and last night. . . so it is trying! \r\n\r\n<p>We need about 12 inches of snowfall in order to start up the lifts again, but at Baker we know this can happen overnight with the right weather pattern so hang in there.    \r\n\r\n<p>Looking back to our weather records from 1976 which was a similar type winter, we received 7 feet of snow in one week in mid February and it just kept on snowing bringing us a huge amount of snow in March as well.  We will be sure to keep you posted.','','9:18 am',1107019301,4,1,1,0,1,1),(146,'Please see below','Other','trace','','trace','',33,'','Calm','Overcast- looks like we may get a bit of snow this afternoon.',20,30,'see below\r\n','Mt. Baker remains closed while we wait on a little more snow, However, we did received a trace of new snow Thursday, Friday and again last night. . . so it is trying! \r\n\r\n<p>We need about 12 inches of snowfall in order to start up the lifts again, but at Baker we know this can happen overnight with the right weather pattern so hang in there.    \r\n\r\n<p>Looking back to our weather records from 1976 which was a similar type winter, we received 7 feet of snow in one week in mid February and it just kept on snowing bringing us a huge amount of snow in March as well.  We will be sure to keep you posted.','','9:18 am',1107105597,4,1,1,0,1,1),(147,'Please see below','Other','trace','','trace','',33,'','Calm','Overcast',20,30,'see below\r\n','Mt. Baker remains closed while we wait on a little more snow, However, we did received a trace of new snow for the last 4 nights. (Thursday, Friday, Saturday AND Sunday)\r\n\r\n<p>So far this season, we have operated 56 days and from this coming weekend forward, we still potentially have 74 days of operation remaining. In an average winter, we typically operate 135 days total, so this means we still have the majority of the season to go.  Stay tuned.\r\n\r\n<p>We need about 12 inches of snowfall in order to start up the lifts again and we will be sure to keep you posted.','','10:37 am',1107196797,4,1,0,0,1,1),(148,'Please see below','Other','trace','','trace','',33,'','Calm','Overcast',20,30,'see below\r\n','Mt. Baker remains closed while we wait on a little more snow, However, we did received a trace of new snow for the last 4 nights. (Thursday, Friday, Saturday AND Sunday)\r\n\r\n<p>So far this season, we have operated 56 days and from this coming weekend forward, we still potentially have 74 days of operation remaining. In an average winter, we typically operate 135 days total, so this means we still have the majority of the season to go.  Stay tuned.\r\n\r\n<p>We need about 12 inches of snowfall in order to start up the lifts again.\r\n\r\n<p>Well keep you posted,\r\n\r\n<p>Your Faithful Snow Searcher','','11:00 am',1107198096,4,1,0,0,1,1),(149,'Please see below','Other','1','','1','',30,'','Calm','Overcast with sun breaks ',20,30,'see below\r\n','Mt. Baker remains closed while we wait on a little more snow, However, we did received an inch of new snow last night and a trace each night since Thursday. . . it\'s trying!  The temp dropped last night as well and we are down to 30 degrees which is a good sign.\r\n\r\n<p>So far this season, we have operated 56 days and from this coming weekend forward, we still potentially have 74 days of operation remaining. In an average winter, we typically operate 135 days total, so this means we still have the majority of the season to go.  Stay tuned.\r\n\r\n<p>We need about 12 inches of snowfall in order to start up the lifts again.\r\n\r\n<p>Well keep you posted.','','9:42 am',1107279932,4,1,0,0,1,1),(150,'Please see below','Other','1','','trace','',36,'','Calm','Sun breaks',20,30,'see below\r\n','Mt. Baker remains closed while we wait on a little more snow, however, the temp has been dropping each night and we have receiv