e rolling our way.  With this very active weather, it’s going to be a bit of a wild ride the next few days, but keep those skis and boards ready because by Tuesday/Wednesday we expect to significant snowfall to move in with LARGE AMOUNTS OF NEW SNOW.\r\n\r\nFOR SATURDAY - MONDAY\r\nIn the meantime . . . Saturday and Sunday look warm and wet, and we are anticipating having to be flexible with how much of the ski area we will operate on Monday, as we anticipate losing some snow with this first warm front.  HOWEVER, on the brighter (and white) side, the freezing level is expected to drop after this first front and it looks like we should be getting snow by Monday morning.  BY TUESDAY WE EXPECT 6 – 10 INCHES OF NEW SNOW.  We are hoping to have both base areas open on Monday, or by Tuesday at the latest depending on when the snow moves in.\r\n\r\nFROM TUESDAY ON IT LOOKS EVEN BETTER\r\nFrom Tuesday on are the days to look forward to for significant snowfall.  How much we get and when depends on the timing of how the storms move over us, but these will likely be the “rally” days as cold air mixes back in . . .just what we like to see!\r\n\r\nSo hang in there, it’s going to be a bit of a bumpy Northwest weather weekend, but the good news is that there is SNOW ON THE HORIZON!\r\n\r\nSKI AREA OPERATION HOURS THE NEXT FEW DAYS:\r\nSaturday Dec 24:  Chairs 1,2,3,5,&6 out of the Heather Meadows Base Area 9:00-3:30\r\n\r\nSunday Dec 25:  The ski area will be CLOSED DEC 25 ONLY for the holiday.\r\n\r\nMonday Dec 26:  Resume daily operation at 9:00 – stay tuned for which chairs and base area will be open.\r\n','','3:30pm',1135381951,2,1,1,0,1,0),(505,'Please see below','9:00 am - 3:30 pm','0','TRACE','0','',43,'','Calm','RAINING',42,63,'MACHINE GROOMED','<B>A SERIES OF FRONTS ARE COMING OUR WAY:</B>\r\nThere is currently a series of large fronts stacked up out in the Pacific and they are rolling our way. With this very active weather, it\'s going to be a bit of a wild ride the nex