ate opening day plans daily on our website and snow report.\r\n<p>\r\nSTAY TUNED!  Check out our Gallery  in the menu above for photos from today on the mountain.','','2:45',1163199152,1,1,1,1,1,0),(891,'Please see below','Other','15','','15','',30,'','Moderate','Snowing heavily!',15,20,'see below','Mt. Baker received 15 inches of new snow in the past 24 hours and with another 2 feet of snow forecasted to fall over the weekend and continued snowfall early next week. \r\n<p>\r\nThe current weather trend combined with the forecasted snowfall has allowed us to set a TENTATIVE OPENING DAY FOR NEXT THURSDAY, NOVEMBER 16th. \r\n<p>\r\nFinal opening day plans will be made sometime late Tuesday or early Wednesday after a significant front is expected to pass over the area. Total snowfall after this front will determine if the ski area will open.\r\n<p>\r\nWe will update opening day plans daily on our website and snow report.\r\n<p>\r\nSTAY TUNED! Check out our Galleries in the menu above for photos from today on the mountain. ','','3:15',1163200682,1,1,0,0,1,0),(892,'Please see below','Other','24','','24','',29,'','Calm','Snowing lightly',31,40,'see below','Wow!  we received 2 FEET OF NEW snow since yesterday morning and it is still snowing lightly.  With 31 INCHES OF SNOW sitting on the ground at Heather Meadows, things are shaping up good!\r\n<p>\r\nWe announced yesterday that we have set a tentative OPENING DAY FOR THURSDAY NOVEMBER 16.\r\n<p>More snow is forecasted through Tuesday and then we anticipate a large system moving in on Wednesday.  We are holding off until Thursday, because a) our crews are busy preping the ski area right now. . .setting out rope lines, grooming and such which will take a few days and b)  we are seeing somewhat conflicting forecasts in regards to a large system expected to move in to the area on Tuesday night/Wednesday.  It looks like this system may possibly carry some warm air with it and we need to see how this will materialize and possibl